description.plain:
Considered as Sébastien’s best work by many, La Ritournelle is an almost 8 minutes long track featuring a complex, yet easy to listen to, melody and one tender loving verse. It gained Sébastien many fans, it was a defining moment in his career.
The impressive drumming was done by Tony Allen.

A shorter version with more singing was released which allowed radio play.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BPWQTLLMAAc

A “ritournelle” is a popular repetitive song.

description.plain:
This song was France’s candidate for the Eurovsion Contest in 2008. It got 47 points and ranked 19th out of 25 songs. Right wing deputee François-Michel Gonnot complained about the song being in english, which created a small polemic at the time. Sébastien responded by changing a few lines in the song.
The performance he gave was a peculiar one.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=d2d2sLzvqCc

It is one of the only songs in Sexuality that doesn’t talk about sex.

It is produced by one half of Daft Punk: Guy-Manuel “Guy-Man” de Homem-Christo.
